Source: luks-root-smartcard-tools
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: JT <jtmoree@users.noreply.github.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.7.0
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/jtmoree-github-com/luks-root-smartcard

Package: luks-root-smartcard-tools
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, cryptsetup-initramfs, initramfs-tools, gnupg, opensc, pcscd, systemd-cryptsetup, libfido2-1
Description: Smartcard root unlock for Debian/Ubuntu
 Provides initramfs hooks and boot scripts that unlock the root volume
 using a smartcard.  Supports FIDO2 (systemd-fido2), TPM2 (systemd-tpm2),
 PKCS#11 (systemd-pkcs11), and GPG/scdaemon (gpg-token or keyfile).
